#: ../../../docs/integrate.rst:10
msgid ""
"Since Pygments 0.9, the distribution ships Markdown_ preprocessor sample "
"code that uses Pygments to render source code in :file:`external/markdown-"
"processor.py`.  You can copy and adapt it to your liking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/integrate.rst:18
msgid "TextMate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/integrate.rst:20
msgid ""
"Antonio Cangiano has created a Pygments bundle for TextMate that allows to "
"colorize code via a simple menu option.  It can be found here_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/integrate.rst:26
msgid "Bash completion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/integrate.rst:28
msgid ""
"The source distribution contains a file ``external/pygments.bashcomp`` that "
"sets up completion for the ``pygmentize`` command in bash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/integrate.rst:32
msgid "wxPython"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/integrate.rst:33
msgid ""
"The `pygments-gui <https://github.com/TEParsons/pygments-gui>`_ plugin adds "
"Pygments functionality to the wxPython package, making it easy to create a "
"wx text control with Pygments highlighting."
msgstr ""

